OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,387,380,120,260,000,100
PN,38605
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F386A1782371886
OL,3,CTranscript reveals moment police
OL,4,Cdiscovered Henry Nowak had been stabbed
OL,6,FIn the transcript, police officer one
OL,7,Fsaid: "Come on mate. That's it, that's
OL,8,Fit. Keeping breathing. Come on."
OL,10,FAccording to the time-stamps, between
OL,11,Ffive minutes and 24 seconds and seven
OL,12,Fminutes and 33 seconds, a female
OL,13,Fpolice officer asks for a torch,
OL,14,Fwanting to make sure Mr Nowak has not
OL,15,Fbeen stabbed, and asks for scissors.
OL,17,FAfter seven minutes and 33 seconds,
OL,18,Fthe officer cuts his clothing and
OL,19,Fpolice officer one asks if he has been
OL,20,Fstabbed there, with an unseen gesture.
OL,26,@oD@GOUpD@`O]
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G5/9
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
